Demon Slayer is a popular manga and anime series about Tanjiro Kamado, a boy whose family is killed by demons. He joins the Demon Slayer Corps to avenge his family and find a cure for his sister, Nezuko, who has become a demon. Tanjiro trains as a swordsman, battling powerful demons and uncovering the secrets of his world. The series captivates audiences with its intense action, emotional storytelling, and vibrant characters. With its iconic art style and strong themes of resilience, friendship, and redemption, "Demon Slayer" has become a global phenomenon, capturing the hearts of fans worldwide.